commit 3094439b6a5f0fcbe07dfa348686e78ccf27b65c
Author: Konstantin <rsboarder@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue May 19 23:17:15 2026 +0400

    Decouple derivations, harden agent CLIs, add Ports and learnings
    
    Major architectural moves that closed entire classes of bug surfaced
    across recent council runs on the bookmatcher monorepo.
    
    Event-sourced derivations (owlex/derivations.py + tests):
    - Long-lived worker started in server.main() owns a process-wide queue
      for analytics writes (pairwise_agreements, position_deltas,
      skill_invocations). Producers (Council, Engine) call emit(event); the
      worker survives individual MCP requests. Shutdown drains with a
      bounded timeout; backfill (dashboard/backfill.py) is the fallback
      when drain times out.
    - Fixes the "fast council loses pairwise" symptom where R1 consensus
      skipped R2 and fire-and-forget tasks were cancelled at event-loop
      teardown before they finished writing.
    
    Subprocess hardening (engine.py):
    - Stream-reader output cap (default 25 MB per stream) kills agents
      that flood stderr without forward progress.
    - Heartbeat (every 30s) logs running/idle/lines per task so silent
      stalls and silent-buffered completions look different in logs.
    - fail_pattern recovery: when a fail pattern fires AFTER stdout has
      content, the task is promoted to COMPLETED with the pattern hit
      stashed in warnings, instead of discarding a complete answer.
      Closes the gemini 429 'MODEL_CAPACITY_EXHAUSTED' answer-loss bug.
    - Recursion fence: OWLEX_COUNCIL_DEPTH is propagated into every
      subprocess; council_ask refuses when non-zero so agents can't spawn
      nested councils via their own MCP.
    
    Cross-layer Protocol (owlex/ports.py):
    - EnginePort declares the exact surface Council uses on TaskEngine.
      Council annotates self._engine: EnginePort. test_engine_port.py adds
      an AST-scan test that fails CI if council.py reaches a method not on
      the Port. Catches the bug class where TaskEngine._log_timing was
      removed but a Council call site kept the reference, throwing
      AttributeError on every council with a subprocess timeout.
    
    Agent CLI integrations:
    - gemini: inject GEMINI_CLI_TRUST_WORKSPACE=true to bypass the
      workspace-trust gate added in gemini-cli 0.39.1 (GHSA-wpqr-6v78-jr5g,
      CVSS 10.0 RCE patch). Without it, headless YOLO downgrades to
      default and exits 55.
    - agreement judge: env-configurable model (OWLEX_AGREEMENT_MODEL,
      default gemini-3-flash) + 90s timeout (OWLEX_AGREEMENT_TIMEOUT) +
      startup probe (probe_agreement_model) that logs [ok]/[WARN] line.
      Catches catalog rotation immediately instead of silently falling
      back to overlap-heuristic for weeks.
    - Resolution value object (owlex/resolution.py): seat/runner/model
      triple with transcript_source dispatch. Skill parser now dispatches
      by runner, not seat — fixes mis-attribution where substituted
      claudeor (running as codex) picked up the parent Claude Code
      session's tool calls.
    
    Test isolation (tests/conftest.py):
    - Autouse _isolate_owlex_home fixture sets OWLEX_HOME to a tmp dir
      per test and resets store + derivations singletons. Cleans up after
      81 MagicMock-poisoned rows of pre-existing prod pollution. Store
      modules now resolve OWLEX_HOME at call time via _owlex_home(),
      not at import time.
    
    Server layout:
    - owlex/server.py (1340 lines) split into owlex/server/ package by
      tool group (_council.py, _sessions.py, _tasks.py, _resources.py,
      _validators.py).
    - store.py thinned from 528 lines to a façade over
      owlex/adapters/repositories/ (calls, councils, scores, pairwise,
      skills). Migrations now ordered SQL files under
      owlex/adapters/db/migrations/.
    - Server stderr is tee'd to ~/.owlex/logs/server-{pid}.log via
      _install_stderr_logging() so every council failure leaves an
      inspectable post-mortem.
    
    Documentation:
    - CLAUDE.md at repo root with architecture map + Learned Patterns
      section.
    - docs/solutions/{architecture,subprocess,testing,protocols,external-tools}/
      per-pattern solution docs.
    - .claude/learnings/{category}/ learning files with YAML frontmatter
      for /pre-flight discovery.
    
    Test suite: 266 passing (+ 41 net new tests covering each guardrail).
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

